My best guess for the source of the error is the fact that stopWithX Resets the heading of the modules instead of setting the desired module states to the X setup

/**

* Stops the drive and turns the modules to an X arrangement to resist movement. The modules will

* return to their normal orientations the next time a nonzero velocity is requested.

*/

public void stopWithX() {

Rotation2d[] headings = new Rotation2d[4];

for (int i = 0; i < 4; i++) {

headings[i] = getModuleTranslations()[i].getAngle();

}

kinematics.resetHeadings(headings);

stop();

}

/** Returns a command to run a quasistatic test in the specified direction. */

public Command sysIdQuasistatic(SysIdRoutine.Direction direction) {

return run(() -> runCharacterization(0.0))

.withTimeout(1.0)

.andThen(sysId.quasistatic(direction));

}

From a quick glance it doesn’t seem like the heading is reset where 0 is forward?
